## Key Patterns

### Unit of Work (UoW)

Each use case receives a UoW that wraps a database transaction. The UoW provides typed access to entity repositories via C++ macros defined in `uow_macros.h`.

**Interface macros** (in `i_{use_case}_uow.h`, pure virtual). **Implementation macros** (in `units_of_work/{use_case}_uow.h`) use the same names without the `DECLARE_` prefix. Both files must declare the same set of entity operations.

#### Always available

| Macro | Generated method |
|-------|------------------|
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_GET(Name)` | `getName(ids) → QList<Name>` |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_GET_ALL(Name)` | `getAllName() → QList<Name>` |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_CREATE_ORPHANS(Name)` | `createOrphanName(items) → QList<Name>` |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_UPDATE(Name)` | `updateName(items) → QList<Name>` |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_REMOVE(Name)` | `removeName(ids) → QList<int>` |

#### Only when entity has an owner (is a child in a relationship)

| Macro | Generated method |
|-------|------------------|
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_CREATE(Name)` | `createName(items, ownerId, index) → QList<Name>` |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_GET_REL_FROM_OWNER(Name)` | `getNameRelationshipsFromOwner(ownerId) → QList<int>` |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_SET_REL_IN_OWNER(Name)` | `setNameRelationshipsInOwner(ids, ownerId)` |

#### Only when entity has forward relationships

| Macro | Generated methods |
|-------|-------------------|
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_RELATIONSHIPS(Name, Rel)` | `getNameRelationship(id, rel) → QList<int>`, `setNameRelationship(id, rel, relatedIds)`, `getNameRelationshipMany(ids, rel) → QHash<int, QList<int>>`, `getNameRelationshipCount(id, rel) → int`, `getNameRelationshipInRange(id, rel, offset, limit) → QList<int>` |

#### Only when entity is undoable

| Macro | Generated methods |
|-------|-------------------|
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_SNAPSHOT(Name)` | `snapshotName(ids) → EntityTreeSnapshot`, `restoreName(snap)` |

#### Composite macros

| Macro | Expands to |
|-------|------------|
| `DECLARE_UOW_ENTITY_CRUD(Name)` | CREATE + CREATE_ORPHANS + GET + GET_ALL + UPDATE + REMOVE + SNAPSHOT + GET_REL_FROM_OWNER + SET_REL_IN_OWNER |
| `DECLARE_UOW_ORPHAN_ENTITY_CRUD(Name)` | CREATE_ORPHANS + GET + GET_ALL + UPDATE + REMOVE + SNAPSHOT (no owner-based create) |

### Controllers

Entity controllers are auto-generated with full CRUD operations. Feature controllers are generated with stubs for custom use cases. All async methods return `QCoro::Task<T>`.

### Namespaces

| Layer | Namespace |
|-------|-----------|
| Common infrastructure | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common` |
| Common entities | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common::Entities` |
| Common database | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common::Database` |
| Common unit of work | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common::UnitOfWork` |
| Common undo/redo | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common::UndoRedo` |
| Entity repos/tables/events | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common::DirectAccess::{Entity}` |
| Entity controllers/DTOs/UoW | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::DirectAccess::{Entity}` |
| Feature controllers/DTOs/UoW/UCs | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::{Feature}` |
| Feature events | `{{ s.global.application_pascal_name }}::Common::Features` |

### Events

Entity changes emit signals through `EventRegistry`. Feature signals go through `FeatureEventRegistry`. `SignalBuffer` defers event emission until after transaction commit.

### Undo/Redo

The `UndoRedoSystem` manages command stacks of `UndoRedoCommand` objects. Controllers wrap use cases into commands via `executeUndoableCommand`, which calls `useCase->execute()`, `useCase->undo()`, and `useCase->redo()`.

For **auto-generated entity CRUD** use cases, `undo()` and `redo()` are pre-built using `EntityTreeSnapshot` (capture state before mutation, restore on undo).

For **custom feature use cases**, the developer must add `undo()` and `redo()` methods to the use case class and implement state capture/restoration manually using the UoW snapshot/restore operations.

### Long Operations

Long-running use cases implement `ILongOperation`. They run on a background thread managed by `LongOperationManager`, with progress reporting and cancellation support.

## Conventions

- **Entity names**: PascalCase in code, snake_case in file paths
- **File naming**: `{snake_name}_controller.h`, `{snake_name}_uc.h`, `dtos.h`
- **One use case per file**: each operation gets its own `.h/.cpp` pair
- **Strong relationships**: cascade delete (owner deletes children)
- **Weak relationships**: reference only (no cascade)
- **Error handling**: throw `std::runtime_error`, catch block handles rollback
- **Prefix path**: `{{ s.global.prefix }}`
